{"questionId":"12277","questionHtml":"<p>The matrices <strong><em>A</em></strong>, <strong><em>B</em></strong>, <strong><em>C</em></strong> and <strong><em>X</em></strong> are all non-singular 3 × 3 matrices.</p>\n<p>Given that <strong><em>A</em></strong><sup><em>–</em>1</sup><strong><em>XB</em></strong> = <strong><em>C</em></strong>, express <strong><em>X</em></strong> in terms of the other matrices.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>AA</em></strong><sup>–1</sup><strong><em>XB</em> </strong>= <strong><em>ΑC</em></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)(A1) </em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>IXBB</em></strong><sup>–1</sup><strong>&nbsp;</strong>= <strong><em>ACB</em></strong><sup>–1</sup>&nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)(A1) </em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>X</em> <em>=</em> <em>ACB</em></strong><sup>–1</sup>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(A1)&nbsp; (C6)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12277","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.48","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"The matrices A, B, C and X are all non-singular 3 × 3 matrices. Given that A–1XB = C, express X in terms of the other matrices.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"48","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}